程序包 io.github.ettoolset.tools.logger

类 Logger

java.lang.Object
io.github.ettoolset.tools.logger.Logger
public class Logger extends Object
The class Logger is a class for logging as it literally shows. Only one Logger can be used in a certain project. If the Logger is used in different classes, you should call

Logger.getDeclaredLogger

to get the declared logger
For more information, plz see the JavaDoc on the functions
作者:
Enderman-Teleporting

  • 嵌套类概要

    嵌套类
    修饰符和类型
    类
    说明
    static enum 
    Logger.Levels
    The levels contain Levels.INFO, Levels.DEBUG and Levels.SEVERE
    For Levels.INFO, you can call: info(), error(), fatal()
    For Levels.DEBUG, you can call: info(), error(), fatal(), debug(), severe(), fine()
    For Levels.SEVERE, you can call: info(), error(), fatal(), severe(), fine()
    If you call the functions that does not match the level you have declared, a LevelNotMatchException will be thrown

    • Logger

      public Logger() throws RepeatedLoggerDeclarationException
      A constructor with no params
      抛出:
      RepeatedLoggerDeclarationException - -> Called when a Logger has already been declared

    • Logger

      public Logger(Logger.Levels level, String fileOutput) throws RepeatedLoggerDeclarationException
      A constructor with params
      参数:
      level - (String) -> Logger level (containing Levels.INFO, Levels.DEBUG and Levels.SEVERE)
      fileOutput - (String) -> The path for a log file that you may want to record the logs in
      抛出:
      RepeatedLoggerDeclarationException - -> Called when a Logger has already been declared
